Business Case: Provide a configuration option to define the external workflow system’s endpoint, authorization type, and credentials. Acceptance Criteria: A new External Workflow configuration service should be developed. It should accept the: External Service Type: ( apiActionEnum )  required   ( added on   based on #5 in. the  Q&A ) There should be the following options acceptable under this parameter( based on their feature flag setting ): External Accounting Validation:  PR_ACCOUNTING_VALIDATION External Workflow:   PR_APPROVAL_PREVIEW, PR_APPROVAL_HISTORY The system should throw the validation error if the user tries to provide any other value. url :  required The External Workflow configuration service should be flexible enough so that based on external system requirements, It should accept one or multiple endpoints. Authorization Type:  required No authorization:  Default value Token Username/Password UnitID info ( in the background. It should not be asked to specify ) This configuration should only become relevant if the External Workflow Augmentation toggle is ON ( refer to  )( This is the answer for #1 in the  Q&A ) If the feature flag is off, the system should throw a validation error when a user tries to provide the endpoint and credentials for the external workflow. ( added on   based on #1 in. the  Q&A ) This configuration should only become relevant if the External Accounting Validation toggle is ON ( refer to   )( This is the answer for #1 in the  Q&A ) If the feature flag is off, the system should throw a validation error when a user tries to provide the endpoint and credentials for the external accounting validation. ( added on   based on #1 in. the  Q&A ) This configuration should enable Vroozi to: Get the external workflow timeline information in real-time and keep the Approval Status UI up to date.  Get the external accounting validation information from the external system. In case of duplicate configuration, the system should throw the validation error. The system should not allow the creation of a redundant entry for the same endpoint for the same service. ( added on   based on #5 in. the  Q&A ) The following parameters should be considered to check the duplication of service configuration: External Service Type URL Authentication Validation Error Messages: ( added on    ) When Feature Toggle is disabled. The message should be “Feature not enabled. Please contact your administrator to enable it before proceeding.“ When API name is duplicated. The message should be “Configuration name already exists. Please provide a unique name.“ When API Action is duplicate The message should be “Duplicate action type found. Only one configuration per action type is allowed.“  For leaving the name field null or empty The message should “Field [name] cannot be null or empty.“ For invalid URL The message should be “Not a valid URL.“ Technical Details:    Internal endpoint: internal-service/9393/external-api-configuration  Payload with token {
