} it is stored in the  external_api_configuration  in the vroozi_webhooks. Note: These credentials are case-sensitive. Q&A:  Integration Team  (                           ) Sr.# Question Response Action Status 1 BE - Validation for enabled feature? 2 BE - Hit the external service and get the response and return, synchronous call? No, we do not need to connect to the service at the time of configuration, we need to store this information properly. 3 Need to have the gateway or connector API as well No, we do not need a way to communicate to external system during configuration, this is already done during the actual invocation of the service. 4 IF there is no endpoint from the external system to validate credentials without the actual payload. 5 Do we need to add the type of the service as well? Yes, I think it should be to make this configuration generic. 6 Can you please confirm the expected behavior for the  url  field? Should the system allow storing plain text if no valid URL is provided, or should it strictly enforce a proper URL format?     It should be URL only field.

Business Case: Develop a new data model to receive and process information regarding the external workflow from the external system. Acceptance Criteria: A new data modal should be developed. This new data modal should accept a consolidated list containing the potential approvers from the external system. This data modal should accept the information from the endpoint specified in the configuration service. ( refer to  ) For NBCU, There should be two endpoints: One for PR when it is in DRAFT state( Preview ) One for the PR when it is in post SUBMITTED state( History ) This data model should allow the FE to display this information on UI in PR Approval Status. {  "Approval Timeline":  [  { Name = David,  ( Name of the approver )       Title = Senior Approver, ( Title of the approver )      SSOiD =1234, ( External System   Unique ID of the approver )      Order = 0, ( Order in which approver’s node should appear on the timeline )    Action/History = Approves, Reject, Any other action ( Action that approver has taken )    Inbox = True/False, ( Document currently assigned to this approver )    Flag =  AND/OR, ( If multiple approvers in the list have the same  Order , it will become a required field ) AND  means approval is required from all the approvers residing in the same order. OR  means approval is required from at least one, or some of the approvers residing in the same order. Required = 2, ( if  Flag  is set to  OR , this field will become relevant. ) If no value is specified, the system should automatically set value = 1. This means approval is required from any approvers residing in the same order. ( A potential use case ) If any value is specified, the system should seek that number of approvals from the approvers residing in the same order. The specified value cannot be equal to or greater than the approvers residing in the same order approvalType = Document Level/Line Item Level, ( To determine if the approval is required for the whole document or any specific line item ) approvalLineItem = 2,3,5, ( Optionally, line item number can be provided   If approvalType = Line Item Level ) workFlowSegment = Sourcing/Financial/Budget/Business/Any other value, ( Our system can optionally accept the information about the segments of the workflow )  },   ], Technical Requirement: {
